body_html:
@arundasan91 Yes, I have updated Xcode to 8.
Here is my environment:

  • Xcode: Version 8.0 (8A218a)
  • iOS: 10.0.1 (14A403)

I can run an application with this change on iOS simulator, and iPhone 6.

As you said,
I built and ran successfully without this change on Xcode 7.3 in the past (2 months or so).
Recently I updated my device's OS from 9 to 10,
and it requires Xcode 8,
then duplicate symbol error happens.

I'm not sure this is caused by some source code change in the repository,
or by Xcode 8.
